# Structured Logging Standard

## Required: ZTA structlog Format
ALL services MUST use structured JSON logging matching zerotrustaudit format.

### Python (structlog)
```python
import structlog
mos_logger = structlog.get_logger()
mos_logger.info("event_name", correlation_id=mos_correlationId, tenant_id=mos_tenantId,
                actor_id=mos_actorId, category="business", phi_safe=True)
```

### C# (Serilog)
```csharp
Log.Information("{@Event}", new { EventName = "event_name", CorrelationId = mosCorrelationId,
    TenantId = mosTenantId, Category = "business", PhiSafe = true });
```

## NEVER Do
- ❌ `print()` or `console.log()` for application logging
- ❌ `logging.info("Patient name: " + name)` — PHI leak!
- ❌ Plain text log lines without structure
- ❌ Log raw PHI/PII values (use IDs/hashes only)

## Log Categories
- `audit`: Mutations, approvals, access to sensitive data → ALWAYS logged, WORM storage
- `business`: Business events, workflow transitions → batched, compressed
- `debug`: Diagnostic info → only when debug mode active, auto-expires 30 min
